WEBVTT

00:05.709 --> 00:08.834
♪ somber music ♪

00:08.834 --> 00:10.583
[Ray] Previously
on  Ray Donovan...

00:10.583 --> 00:11.208
[phone rings]

00:13.291 --> 00:15.542
- Bridge.
- I know you poisoned him.

00:15.542 --> 00:17.917
You poisoned him
so Mom could have his spot.

00:17.917 --> 00:19.500
[Bridget]
And now he's gonna die.

00:19.500 --> 00:21.959
That surgery was brutal,
wasn't it?

00:21.959 --> 00:23.333
I never got the surgery.

00:23.333 --> 00:24.667
You're in remission.

00:24.667 --> 00:27.125
- Yeah.
- So it worked.

00:29.333 --> 00:32.000
- I killed her.
- No, you didn't.

00:32.000 --> 00:33.750
- She would've lived.
- You don't know that.

00:33.750 --> 00:36.458
She didn't want the surgery.

00:36.458 --> 00:38.375
We got a little problem
with Avi Rudin.

00:38.375 --> 00:40.458
- We?
- Yeah, we.

00:40.458 --> 00:43.166
You were supposed to
take care of things.

00:43.166 --> 00:45.291
I'm not killing Avi, Frank.

00:45.875 --> 00:48.667
Wallet, cell phone,
and your fuckin' bag.

00:48.667 --> 00:51.583
You guys--oh!
Uh!

00:51.583 --> 00:54.000
You had $1 million
in your daughter's diaper bag?

00:54.000 --> 00:56.125
I know it sounds unusual,
but look,

00:56.125 --> 00:57.375
[Bunchy] I was going to a big
real estate transaction, okay?

00:57.375 --> 01:00.667
I don't know what arrangements
you made with my son,

01:00.667 --> 01:02.792
but my services are included.

01:02.792 --> 01:03.959
- So what do I owe you?
- I've been getting

01:03.959 --> 01:05.542
some excellent feedback

01:05.542 --> 01:06.417
on this little film
that I wrote.

01:06.417 --> 01:09.125
Mr. Donovan, this is not
how things work.

01:09.125 --> 01:11.000
- You, let's go.
- Fuck are you talking about?

01:11.000 --> 01:12.500
You're coming with me.

01:12.500 --> 01:13.583
Hey, Frank,
you made your point.

01:13.583 --> 01:15.417
- Let's--let's talk this over.
- What's going on?

01:15.417 --> 01:16.625
Come on, let's go.

01:16.625 --> 01:20.208
He threatened me with four
consecutive life sentences.

01:20.208 --> 01:20.750
I'm taking care of it.

01:20.750 --> 01:23.792
♪ edgy music ♪

01:23.792 --> 01:25.458
[grunts]

01:27.000 --> 01:28.917
- [siren wailing]
- [Avi] What is that?

01:28.917 --> 01:30.083
- [agent] DEA agent!
- [agent] DEA! Step away from--

01:30.083 --> 01:32.917
- [gunfire]
- [indistinct shouting]

01:32.917 --> 01:35.250
[man] Watch your six!

01:35.250 --> 01:36.625
[gunfire]

01:36.625 --> 01:39.041
[man] We've gotta
get the dough!

01:39.041 --> 01:41.083
[gunfire continues]

01:41.083 --> 01:42.500
[engine turns]

01:42.500 --> 01:47.291
♪♪♪

01:58.417 --> 02:02.917
[car engine revving]

02:02.917 --> 02:04.291
[tires screech]

02:08.083 --> 02:11.083
[panting]
Ay, dios mio.

02:13.000 --> 02:14.542
[tires screeching]

02:14.542 --> 02:16.709
[horn blaring]

02:22.583 --> 02:24.500
[tires screeching]

02:27.250 --> 02:30.458
[brakes squeal]

02:30.458 --> 02:32.000
[engine stops]

02:51.542 --> 02:53.083
Ay! [mutters] Oh!

02:53.083 --> 02:55.917
- [tire iron clangs]
- [coughing]

02:55.917 --> 02:57.500
Ahh!

02:57.500 --> 02:59.125
[screams]

02:59.125 --> 03:01.166
Hey! [muffled yelling]

03:01.166 --> 03:05.000
[pounding on trunk,
muffled yelling]

03:05.000 --> 03:07.333
[muffled yelling]

03:07.333 --> 03:10.333
♪ tense music ♪

03:10.333 --> 03:12.125
♪♪♪

03:12.125 --> 03:15.333
[continues pounding,
yelling indistinctly]

03:15.333 --> 03:19.458
♪♪♪

03:21.542 --> 03:24.333
[muffled yelling continues]

03:24.333 --> 03:28.500
♪♪♪

03:37.417 --> 03:40.417
♪ edgy music ♪

03:40.417 --> 03:45.000
♪♪♪

03:45.000 --> 03:46.333
[wood slides, thuds]

03:47.709 --> 03:50.375
I've--I've had a few, Father.
Is that all right?

03:50.375 --> 03:51.917
[priest] It won't be
the first time

03:51.917 --> 03:55.125
someone's been drunk
in confession.

03:55.125 --> 03:56.542
I didn't say I was drunk.
I said I had a few.

03:59.041 --> 04:01.291
Unburden yourself, my son.

04:01.291 --> 04:02.208
[sighs]
In the name of the Father,

04:02.208 --> 04:04.375
the Son,
and the Holy Spirit.

04:04.375 --> 04:08.375
My last confession
was, uh, four months ago.

04:08.375 --> 04:10.417
Tell me your sins.

04:12.583 --> 04:14.709
My--

04:14.709 --> 04:17.291
my brother's wife--

04:17.291 --> 04:18.083
Yes?

04:18.083 --> 04:22.041
The thoughts I had...

04:22.041 --> 04:24.417
and the things I done...

04:24.417 --> 04:26.083
- My son?
- Well, I didn't think

04:26.083 --> 04:27.750
that I needed to confess,

04:27.750 --> 04:30.667
'cause I got shot
and I nearly died.

04:30.667 --> 04:32.875
But my sister-in-law...

04:32.875 --> 04:35.792
her name was Abby.

04:36.375 --> 04:39.208
And she got cancer.

04:39.208 --> 04:41.583
And those--those thoughts,
they came back.

04:44.333 --> 04:48.250
And the cancer got so bad...

04:48.250 --> 04:50.458
that she wanted to kill herself.

04:51.750 --> 04:54.458
Your sister-in-law Abby,

04:54.458 --> 04:57.250
did she take her own life?

05:02.083 --> 05:05.041
You always hurt
the ones you love.

05:06.834 --> 05:08.959
And the ones you love...

05:08.959 --> 05:11.625
they always hurt you.

05:13.041 --> 05:15.667
Are you worried about her soul?

05:15.667 --> 05:17.542
[Terry chuckles]

05:17.542 --> 05:20.458
Abby's in heaven, Father.

05:20.458 --> 05:21.458
I know she is.

05:24.792 --> 05:26.834
God does forgive.

05:26.834 --> 05:29.041
It's my own soul
I'm worried about.

05:29.041 --> 05:32.083
♪ somber music ♪

05:32.083 --> 05:34.917
♪ ♪

05:34.917 --> 05:36.917
[door creaks open]

05:41.125 --> 05:43.917
I gotta tell your father
what I done.

05:48.291 --> 05:51.667
If Landry comes by, call me.

05:51.667 --> 05:53.458
- And if he doesn't?
- What?

05:53.458 --> 05:55.000
Come by.
Can I still call you?

05:55.000 --> 05:57.625
Come on, let me make you
that dinner later

05:57.625 --> 05:58.333
I never got around to.

05:58.333 --> 06:00.750
[Gustavo] Natalie, darling.

06:00.750 --> 06:03.458
Hm. Missed you.

06:03.458 --> 06:04.500
I was only gone a couple days.

06:04.500 --> 06:07.667
- Couple days too many.
- [chuckles]

06:07.667 --> 06:09.625
We're going to turn you
into a phoenix,

06:09.625 --> 06:11.500
a beautiful phoenix.

06:11.500 --> 06:14.083
- [laughs] Hello, handsome.
- Hey, Gustavo.

06:14.875 --> 06:15.750
Do you two know each other?

06:15.750 --> 06:17.875
I know everyone.
Now, come with me.

06:17.875 --> 06:18.709
I'm gonna get you
ready to be dead

06:18.709 --> 06:21.083
so that you can
rise from the ashes.

06:21.083 --> 06:22.834
- [Natalie] How are you?
- [woman] Good, how are you?

06:22.834 --> 06:23.583
- [Gustavo] Move, move.
- [woman] I'll see you

06:23.583 --> 06:26.375
- over there.
- [Natalie] Okay.

06:26.375 --> 06:27.959
[Gustavo] Hold on.

06:31.875 --> 06:35.333
We have enough black superheroes
already, man.

06:35.333 --> 06:37.709
No, that was the easy part.

06:37.709 --> 06:40.125
Black superheroes
are every day.

06:40.125 --> 06:42.041
This is what I'm thinking.

06:42.041 --> 06:45.709
Gay black superhero.

06:45.709 --> 06:47.709
Hear me out.

06:47.709 --> 06:49.417
Yeah, I know you like it.
You wanna know how I know?

06:49.417 --> 06:51.333
'Cause I spoke to Landry
already about it

06:51.333 --> 06:53.875
and he told you to like it.

06:53.875 --> 06:57.166
What I wanna know--
is he gonna make the shit?

06:57.166 --> 07:00.834
Okay. Yeah.

07:00.834 --> 07:04.125
Feel you.

07:04.125 --> 07:05.959
We'll talk.

07:05.959 --> 07:07.125
- [beep]
- [chuckles]

07:07.125 --> 07:08.625
Easy peasy.

07:09.250 --> 07:12.250
Daryll Donovan. Right?

07:12.250 --> 07:13.417
Yeah, man. What's good?

07:13.417 --> 07:17.208
Hey. Antoine A'Shawn Anderson.

07:20.000 --> 07:22.875
Jay's really excited
about the project.

07:22.875 --> 07:25.125
- What?
- Yeah, I like it, too.

07:25.125 --> 07:28.166
It's good. Bank robbing.

07:28.166 --> 07:30.542
Family. Love of a dying child.

07:30.542 --> 07:33.166
It's good shit,
it's good shit.

07:33.166 --> 07:35.208
- Four Leaf?
- Mm-hmm.

07:35.208 --> 07:38.166
Thing is...

07:38.166 --> 07:40.792
Jay can't play
a bank robber from Southie.

07:40.792 --> 07:43.250
Ehh...why not?

07:43.250 --> 07:45.959
It's been done
a million times.

07:45.959 --> 07:47.458
Yeah, we've seen
that movie before, haven't we?

07:47.458 --> 07:49.291
Yeah, I--I mean, I guess,
right?

07:49.291 --> 07:52.166
Yeah, but don't you worry.

07:52.166 --> 07:55.417
Jay is very sensitive
to your father's creative thing

07:55.417 --> 07:57.291
and his intention.

07:57.291 --> 07:59.667
Antoine, Mr. Donovan,
Jay is ready for you now.

08:01.083 --> 08:03.792
Come on.

08:07.417 --> 08:08.834
[Antoine] All right,
get you some bu--

08:08.834 --> 08:10.959
Let a nigga butter that.
Let a--

08:19.250 --> 08:21.166
[hinges squeaking]

08:21.166 --> 08:23.041
[soft thud]

08:27.166 --> 08:30.000
[exhales deeply]

08:34.250 --> 08:35.834
You have breakfast?

08:35.834 --> 08:36.917
- No.
- [Jay] How 'bout

08:36.917 --> 08:39.500
- a butter coffee?
- [Antoine] Oh, yes, please.

08:39.500 --> 08:41.041
[Daryll] A what?

08:41.041 --> 08:42.667
Maia, three butter coffees,
please.

08:42.667 --> 08:44.458
Of course.

08:44.458 --> 08:47.583
[door opens, closes]

08:47.583 --> 08:49.083
Mm, hm.

08:49.083 --> 08:50.458
- You two met?
- Yeah, outside.

08:50.458 --> 08:52.834
Antoine gave you
the lowdown?

08:52.834 --> 08:54.500
- No.
- [Antoine] I was actually

08:54.500 --> 08:57.959
just about to do that.
[chuckles]

08:57.959 --> 09:00.333
Harlem, 1970s.

09:00.333 --> 09:03.250
Jay plays Michael Abdul Rahim.

09:03.250 --> 09:05.333
Down on his luck
father of four.

09:05.333 --> 09:07.041
Just back from Nam.

09:07.041 --> 09:09.709
Turns to bank robbing
when his son gets in debt

09:09.709 --> 09:11.709
with a white mob boss.

09:11.709 --> 09:14.291
But...instead of
paying off the mob

09:14.291 --> 09:16.041
with the white man's money,

09:16.041 --> 09:18.125
he murders them,

09:18.125 --> 09:21.458
one by one by one.

09:22.458 --> 09:25.417
Keeps the cash.
Uses it...

09:25.417 --> 09:28.750
to open
a veteran hospital in Harlem.

09:28.750 --> 09:32.000
[laughs] Wow. I mean--

09:32.000 --> 09:34.041
[laughs]
It definitely sounds dope.

09:34.041 --> 09:36.208
- Oh, it's dope.
- But, uh, you know,

09:36.208 --> 09:37.875
- that's not my father's story.
- Oh, Mickey gets

09:37.875 --> 09:39.500
- a "story by" credit.
- A what?

09:39.500 --> 09:41.041
Shared with Antoine.
Antoine writes it.

09:41.041 --> 09:42.458
I'ma write that shit.

09:43.500 --> 09:45.834
Look, Jay, uh,
Mickey's not gonna go for it.

09:45.834 --> 09:49.583
That's why we need a smart
producer like yourself, Daryll.

09:49.583 --> 09:53.083
Keep your father in line.
Make sure he's not a problem.

09:55.166 --> 09:57.083
- A producer.
- There's always room

09:57.083 --> 09:58.917
in the boat for a man
who can massage a problem.

09:58.917 --> 10:02.291
Look, you tell your old man
that's where it's at.

10:02.291 --> 10:04.542
We'll put your name
above the line.

10:04.542 --> 10:07.917
And pay you...accordingly.

10:09.917 --> 10:11.750
- Huh.
- [laughs]

10:11.750 --> 10:13.417
Antoine, give me a sec
with my man, please.

10:13.417 --> 10:15.083
Yeah, sure!

10:18.667 --> 10:20.542
[chuckles]

10:20.542 --> 10:23.166
- Um, Mickey--
- That racist piece of shit.

10:23.166 --> 10:24.917
He wrote the worst fuckin'
script in history.

10:26.834 --> 10:30.000
Now, my man Triple A cleaned it
up, made it a Jay White picture.

10:30.000 --> 10:31.041
We'll shoot it fast.

10:31.041 --> 10:33.041
And your father's gonna
give me those tapes,

10:33.041 --> 10:33.959
and we can all be on our way.

10:33.959 --> 10:36.458
- Hey, look, Jay--
- Hey, you make him

10:36.458 --> 10:38.500
see the light,
then we can all get out of this

10:38.500 --> 10:40.125
a little bit better
than we was before.

10:41.917 --> 10:43.917
You feel me?

10:55.583 --> 10:57.792
- You all right?
- Yeah. Your father's here.

11:00.500 --> 11:03.000
- What's he want?
- He didn't say.

11:11.667 --> 11:12.959
What's up, Mick?

11:17.500 --> 11:20.208
They got Bunchy.

11:20.208 --> 11:21.917
Who got Bunchy?

11:21.917 --> 11:25.041
Frank Barnes arrested him
for that shit in Primm.

11:26.458 --> 11:30.709
Ray, he came to me--Barnes.

11:32.417 --> 11:35.709
He came to me, asked me
to--to kill Avi.

11:38.458 --> 11:40.000
What are you talking about?

11:40.000 --> 11:40.792
I tried to change his mind,
I tried to--

11:40.792 --> 11:43.250
Why would Barnes
wanna kill Avi?

11:43.250 --> 11:46.500
The DEA, I think.

11:46.500 --> 11:48.959
They got into business together,
Avi and Barnes.

11:48.959 --> 11:51.041
You stupid motherfucker.

11:52.792 --> 11:55.500
- [sighs]
- Barnes arrested Bunchy.

11:55.500 --> 11:58.291
To force my hand, Ray.

11:58.291 --> 12:01.000
To force my hand
into killing him.

12:15.208 --> 12:18.417
Where's Avi?

12:18.417 --> 12:21.041
I lost him.

12:21.041 --> 12:23.542
There was a mix-up,
and I lost him.

12:23.542 --> 12:26.542
Every time, Mick.

12:26.542 --> 12:29.792
Every fuckin' time.

12:29.792 --> 12:32.291
I never meant to get Bunchy
into nothing.

12:34.250 --> 12:35.375
[sighs]

12:35.375 --> 12:38.417
♪ somber music ♪

12:38.417 --> 12:44.291
♪♪♪

12:46.834 --> 12:47.959
[sighs]

12:49.875 --> 12:52.375
Frank Barnes, please.

12:54.333 --> 12:57.333
I need to talk.

12:57.333 --> 13:00.583
Yeah.

13:00.583 --> 13:02.417
All right.

13:02.417 --> 13:06.000
I can meet you there.

13:06.000 --> 13:07.417
I'll come with you.

13:07.417 --> 13:10.917
No, you won't.

13:10.917 --> 13:12.750
Stay right where
you fuckin' are.

13:14.375 --> 13:16.709
I wish it were me
that was gone.

13:16.709 --> 13:20.291
I wish I could trade
myself for all of them.

13:20.291 --> 13:22.750
Everyone I hurt.

13:24.959 --> 13:26.375
What?

13:26.375 --> 13:29.583
♪ edgy music ♪

13:29.583 --> 13:34.542
♪♪♪

13:34.542 --> 13:37.709
[indistinct chatter]

13:55.166 --> 13:59.333
[man] I know, but
break these guys up, all right?

13:59.333 --> 14:01.041
[indistinct chatter continues]

14:06.500 --> 14:10.125
Fuck you want?

14:10.125 --> 14:11.667
My money.

14:11.667 --> 14:13.500
I ain't never seen your ugly ass

14:13.500 --> 14:15.500
in my entire blessed life.

14:15.500 --> 14:18.709
Railhead Subs.

14:19.917 --> 14:22.959
Yeah? Hm.

14:22.959 --> 14:25.208
I prefer Hungry Harry's.

14:26.750 --> 14:28.834
I'm not fucking around here.

14:28.834 --> 14:30.750
No?

14:30.750 --> 14:31.959
You oughta try
the Club Supreme.

14:35.208 --> 14:38.041
I want...my money

14:38.041 --> 14:40.125
from the robbery.

14:40.125 --> 14:42.542
Robbery, huh?

14:42.542 --> 14:45.792
Hm. Sorry, chief. I'm in here
for stealing copper wire.

14:45.792 --> 14:48.792
You do not wanna fuck with me.

14:48.792 --> 14:51.375
Why don't you step back,
ginger?

14:51.375 --> 14:54.041
I don't know you or what
the fuck you talking about.

14:54.041 --> 14:56.375
- Stand up.
- [laughs]

14:56.375 --> 14:58.542
You big orangutan motherfucker.

14:58.542 --> 15:00.667
- Now!
- [guard] Hey!

15:00.667 --> 15:02.542
Knock it off.

15:02.542 --> 15:04.041
Oh, sorry, Deputy.
Just had a little accident.

15:04.041 --> 15:07.291
[guard]
You, move to a different table.

15:07.291 --> 15:08.667
Now!

15:08.667 --> 15:10.834
You heard the man.

15:11.458 --> 15:13.250
[guard]
You, pick that up.

15:13.250 --> 15:14.542
♪ tense music ♪

15:14.542 --> 15:16.959
Fuckin' monkey boy.

15:16.959 --> 15:21.125
♪♪♪

15:31.500 --> 15:33.917
[exhales]

15:33.917 --> 15:35.500
[mutters under breath]

15:37.750 --> 15:38.250
Pop.

15:40.917 --> 15:42.667
The hell happened to you?

15:42.667 --> 15:43.792
Nothin'.

15:43.792 --> 15:44.917
I been calling, I been textin'.

15:44.917 --> 15:46.959
You might wanna
get a shower, man.

15:46.959 --> 15:47.583
You look like crap.

15:47.583 --> 15:49.250
I had a long night.

15:51.750 --> 15:55.083
I...have some good news.

15:55.083 --> 15:56.250
Oh, yeah?

15:56.250 --> 15:57.750
Oh, yeah.

15:57.750 --> 16:01.125
Our boy, Jay White,

16:01.125 --> 16:02.250
loves Four Leaf.

16:03.166 --> 16:05.125
- Oh, yeah?
- Oh, yeah.

16:05.125 --> 16:07.125
[chuckling]

16:07.125 --> 16:09.208
Oh, yeah, he's bringing in
a top-notch writer

16:09.208 --> 16:10.917
to help spruce it up.

16:10.917 --> 16:12.959
- Spruce it up?
- You know,

16:12.959 --> 16:15.083
make it
a Jay White picture.

16:15.083 --> 16:18.000
See, that right there
is just a concept

16:18.000 --> 16:20.750
to, uh, you know,
help suit our guy.

16:20.750 --> 16:23.500
Harlem? In the 1970s.

16:23.500 --> 16:25.750
Mobsters, Nam vets, afros.

16:25.750 --> 16:30.250
Says here Michael's black.

16:32.083 --> 16:32.792
What'd you expect?

16:32.792 --> 16:34.875
"Story by Mickey Donovan

16:34.875 --> 16:38.542
and Antoine A'Shawn Anderson."

16:38.542 --> 16:39.875
Yeah.

16:39.875 --> 16:42.667
That guy right there's
a real deal.

16:42.667 --> 16:44.458
One of Hollywood's top writers.

16:44.458 --> 16:46.959
[sighs]

16:46.959 --> 16:49.250
- Antoine A'Shawn.
- Mm-hmm.

16:49.250 --> 16:51.333
Fuck him.

16:51.333 --> 16:55.166
Jay White ain't making Michael
into a black veteran in Harlem.

16:55.166 --> 16:59.083
He's a Southie bank robber
for fuck's sake.

16:59.083 --> 17:00.166
Pop, what are you talking about?

17:00.166 --> 17:01.667
This could be huge!

17:01.667 --> 17:04.000
This is it.

17:04.000 --> 17:05.291
Take me home, Daryll.

17:07.959 --> 17:09.667
I gotta get some sleep.

17:09.667 --> 17:12.583
Pop, we just landed Jay White!

17:19.917 --> 17:23.834
[old-timey music playing
on stereo]

17:23.834 --> 17:28.959
♪♪♪

17:32.291 --> 17:35.417
- So Mickey came crying to you
to fix his problems, huh?

